Welcome to #cancerchat. I'm @debecca, I have Bipolar Disorder & was diagnosed with #breastcancer at 32. Will be hosting tonight 9-10pm.
First question - how did friends / family react to your cancer diagnosis? Did they treat you differently? #cancerchat
RT @EverydayAbleism: First question - how did friends / family react to your cancer diagnosis? Did they treat you differently? #cancerchat
My experience is that friends rallied at cancer diagnosis (much more so than with Bipolar!) but only true friends saw it through #cancerchat
@EverydayAbleism the road and didn't even speak to me #cancerchat
@EverydayAbleism yes some treated me different, some haven't - some fell by the wayside & didn't gv a monkeys! Some crossed ovr #cancerchat
RT @EverydayAbleism: My experience is that friends rallied at cancer diagnosis (much more so than with Bipolar!) but only true friends saw …
RT @EverydayAbleism: Welcome to #cancerchat. I'm @debecca, I have Bipolar Disorder & was diagnosed with #breastcancer at 32. Will be hostin…
@EverydayAbleism absolutely, I totally agree. I have one friend who texted me every day without fail and it made a difference #cancerchat

.@EverydayAbleism I must say that having secondary #breastcancer is like having a second child.. Some just aren't bothered! #cancerchat
RT @abcdiagnosis: @EverydayAbleism absolutely, I totally agree. I have one friend who texted me every day without fail and it made a differ…
.@debecca @EverydayAbleism I have found that with secondary #breastcancer that most are totally uneducated and don't understand #cancerchat
@abcdiagnosis Yes, I went through treatment with no partner/family & those friends who took me in and cared for me saved my life #cancerchat
.@debecca @EverydayAbleism what it means ie treatable but not curable #breastcancer #bcmets #mbcaware #cancerchat

.@EverydayAbleism it's the ones you don't expect to do stuff who do and shocked by the ones that don't give support! #cancerchat
@EverydayAbleism I've found with the charity bike ride I'm doing, I'm surprised to find people who I thought didn't even like me #cancerchat
.@EverydayAbleism have sponsored me and that's quite a surprise! It's changed my perception of people for sure #cancerchat

Speaking of reactions, what's the worst you had? Mine? 

"Dad, I've got cancer!"
"I DON'T NEED THIS RIGHT NOW!"

Er, nor do I?! #cancerchat
@EverydayAbleism thank god for friends!! And thanks for people who understand x #cancerchat

RT @EverydayAbleism: Speaking of reactions, what's the worst you had? Mine? 

"Dad, I've got cancer!"
"I DON'T NEED THIS RIGHT NOW!"

Er, n…
RT @abcdiagnosis: @EverydayAbleism thank god for friends!! And thanks for people who understand x #cancerchat
So, what was the strangest reaction you had to an external indicator of your cancer, for example bald head or Hickman line? #cancerchat
.@EverydayAbleism no way!!! That's awful! I can't say I've had a reaction like that.. #cancerchat
RT @EverydayAbleism: So, what was the strangest reaction you had to an external indicator of your cancer, for example bald head or Hickman …
@EverydayAbleism ah.. Well recently I had my portacath accessed by a nurse in phlebotomy and I told her I didn't like it as it #cancerchat
I hated total strangers coming up to me on a rare night out saying, "You're such an inspiration!" because I had a bald head #cancerchat
@EverydayAbleism was a lump and she said that I could always tell people it's just a boil?! Hmm... Er no #cancerchat
RT @EverydayAbleism: I hated total strangers coming up to me on a rare night out saying, "You're such an inspiration!" because I had a bald…

@EverydayAbleism to get on with it... No choice #cancerchat

.@hellboy8700 you've just reminded me my ENT surgeon, when I told him they found cancer in lymph nodes 'oh dear, dear, dear' #cancerchat
Last qu (as I think everyone is watching the football!)... Did having cancer make you view disability differently in general? #cancerchat

RT @hellboy8700: @EverydayAbleism similar.found more empathy re cancer then my epilepsy. But cancer has made more vocal about my epilepsy #…

Just before I go... I have grown to loathe:

* inspiration 
* fighter / battler / brave 
* cancer victim
* pinkification

#cancerchat
